The speaker of this oration defended his wife by noting that she was born on St. Patrick’s Day, and
the Irish never quit. A “two-year-old Oldsmobile” and loans from Riggs Bank were recounted in this
speech, which was a response to concerns that a fund used to reimburse its speaker for travel expenses was
a source of corruption. Its speaker noted that Pat did not have a mink coat, but that his children loved
the central figure and would be keeping it. For the point, name this 1952 televised speech by Richard
Nixon, named for the cocker spaniel he intended to keep.=====
